Advanced Time Series Forecasting with Attention-Based Neural Networks

(Synthetic Multivariate Dataset – Transformer Model)

1. Dataset Description & Generation

To satisfy the requirement of a complex multivariate time series, a synthetic dataset was programmatically generated. Synthetic generation was chosen to ensure controlled seasonality, trend, noise, and feature interdependence, enabling meaningful attention interpretation.

Dataset Properties

Time steps: 1,200

Number of features: 5

Characteristics:

Multiple seasonal patterns

Long-term trend

Feature correlations

Gaussian noise

Feature Description
Feature	Description
F1	Primary sinusoidal signal (period = 24)
F2	Secondary cosine signal (period = 12)
F3	Linear trend + noise
F4	Lagged interaction of F1 & F2
F5	High-frequency seasonal component
2. Model Architecture

A Transformer-based neural network was implemented using PyTorch.
The architecture includes:

Input projection layer

Multi-head self-attention encoder

Feed-forward layers

Dropout regularization

Linear output head

This model was selected due to its ability to capture long-range temporal dependencies and learn feature importance via attention weights, satisfying the project’s advanced modeling requirement.

