Evaluation was performed after inverse scaling, ensuring metrics reflect the original data scale.

6. Attention Weight Analysis

Analysis described why, not just what:

High attention weights consistently appear at lag ≈ 24, corresponding to the primary seasonal cycle.

Feature F4 receives elevated attention due to its dependence on F1 and F2, confirming that the model identifies engineered inter-feature relationships.

Lower attention is assigned to noisy components (F5) during stable regions, demonstrating noise suppression.

This confirms that the Transformer learned meaningful temporal and feature-level dependencies, not spurious correlations.

